## 📈 What Made Day 22 Different?

Previous projects focused heavily on CRUD operations and localStorage.

This project introduced a different type of frontend logic:

- Managing application state
- Moving sequentially through data
- Nested arrays and objects
- Dynamic question rendering
- Checking user answers
- Providing immediate visual feedback
- Tracking a live score
- Calculating percentages
- Controlling a multi-step application flow

This helped strengthen my understanding of how JavaScript manages an interactive user experience.

